CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 8 reads:"Frogs' Wives Entertain Glamorously at Loendi - Here They Are! - Frogs' wives and guests smile prettily for the cameraman during their charming coffee hour held at Loendi Club Monday night. Right photo, seated, Mrs. John Stanton, Miss Ethel West, Mmes. Jared Arter, and Henry Lindsay.  Standing, Mmes. Samuel Milai, Charles Rickmond, Olive [Weis] of West Virginia, Nann Rucker of Los Angeles, M.V. Holland of Cleveland.  Roland Saywer, George Little, Byron Peters and Howard Rickmond... - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left, seated: Mrs. John Stanton, Ethel West, Mrs. Jared Arter, Mrs. Henry Lindsay; standing: Mrs. Samuel Milai, J. Rickmond, Olive Weis, Nann Rucker, M. V. Holland, Aileen Eckstein Sawyer, Mrs. George Little, Mrs. Byron Peters, and Mrs. Howard Rickmond, gathered in Loendi Club for FROGS wives coffee hour
